ExecDesc.value: Microsoft Internet Explorer Error Handling Code Execution (IPv6 Version)

EngDesc.value: A memory corruption vulnerability exists in certain versions of Microsoft Internet Explorer. The vulnerability is due to the way Internet Explorer handles certain error situations. Remote attackers can exploit this vulnerability by persuading target users to visit a specially crafted web page. Successful exploitation would allow the attacker to execute arbitrary code on the vulnerable client system, in the context of the logged in user. (IPv6 Version)
